	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_25961279"><p>No.</p><p>(1)   His argument is that to discuss "software engineering" is as silly as to discuss "algebra engineering" or "formula engineering" in math courses.  A program is simply a formula to be executed - nothing more - says the Computer Science professor.</p><p>(2)  Programs manipulate numbers.  Mathematic formulae manipulate numbers.  It's an entirely reasonable conclusion that he has reached that a program is merely a formula.</p><p>(3) Putting pretty pictures on screen or manipulating airplane surfaces (my specialty) is still just formula execution.</p></div>
