	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_25959787"><p>I don't know what you think FrontPage has to do with anything. Perhaps you're just trolling?</p><p>Software engineers should understand use case analys, user interface design, project management and finance, and many other important subjects "computer science" curricula ignore while beating students over the head with details theory. Understanding issues of scalability is good (though often <b>actual testing</b> is used in the engineering world for practical reasons), but we don't need four years of that while ignoring more important topics.</p><p>I'm not saying exhaustive study of the mathematical theory of computation is bad. I'm saying students are badly served at most universities by focusing on that at the expense of other topics.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_25959787">
